OL,4,CChina's 'midnight patrol' cracks down
OL,5,Con young gamers
OL,6, Chinese gaming giant Tencent is rolling
OL,7, out facial recognition to stop children
OL,8, playing between 22:00 and 08:00.
OL,10,FThe "midnight-patrol" technology will
OL,11,Fstop "tricks" circumventing the
OL,12,Fgovernment curfew, introduced in 2019
OL,13,Fwith a cap on what young gamers could
OL,14,Fspend on in-game transactions, it says.
OL,16,FThe bans require gamers to register
OL,17,Fwith their official IDs, linked to a
OL,18,Fnational database.
OL,20,FBut children have reportedly been using
OL,21,Fadults' IDs instead of their own.
